name: University Community Health Center
review_text:
Today I brought my brother in with a denture issue. We were met with a warm welcome first thing. I started to fill out his information and had a few questions and the assistant explained it well and didn‚Äôt make me feel bad for asking. We had a relatively short wait and we were brought back with precision help, as he is wheelchair bound. She got us all prepared for Dr Lim. What a gem she is :) Close to perfect. Even though this office does not handle dentures she still took the time to give him a full exam and made notes to send along with a Referral!

From this experience I felt prompted to ask what Insurance they accepted for myself. That is how confident I feel about this great dental office, Doctor and staff!

name: University Community Health Center
review_text: I can't say nothing but positive things about staff at this place. They are always courteous and helpful over the phone and in person. My favorite person there  is NP Adriana Cornejo. She has been taking care of my two daughters for over two years now.  She is professional, caring, very good with children. Despite her busy schedule, whenever I call and leave a message for her ,she would call me back within 3-4 hours.  She would take care of any small things related to my daughters' health including calling pharmacies to make sure they have a specific medication for my daughters.
